{% block head %}
<style>
#home .api {display: flex; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 20px 0}
#home .api p {margin: 2px 0 0}
#home .api > div {width: 500px;}
#home .api > a{margin-left: auto; padding: 4px; border: 1px solid #ddd;border-radius:4px;display:inline-block;padding: 5px 10px;align-self:flex-start}
#home .api > a:hover{background:#ff40ae;color:#fff;text-decoration: none}
#home .api code, p code, li code, aside code {padding: 0px 3px;border-radius: 4px;background: #f7fafc; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)}
</style>
{% endblock %}
<h1>Zig Utility Library</h1>
<p>The purpose of this library is to enhance Zig's standard library. Much of zul wraps Zig's std to provide simpler APIs for common tasks (e.g. reading lines from a file). In other cases, new functionality has been added (e.g. a UUID type).</p>

<p>Besides Zig's standard library, there are no dependencies. Most functionality is contained within its own file and can easily be copy and pasted into an existing library or project.</p>

{%- for post in collections.sorted %}
{%- set meta = postMeta(post) -%}
<div class=api>
	<div>
		<code>{{ post.data.title }}</code>
		<p>{{ meta.desc }}</p>
	</div>
	{% if meta.example %}<a class=example href="{{ env.baseURL }}{{post.url}}#example">example</a>{% endif %}
	<a href="{{ env.baseURL }}{{post.url}}">docs</a>
</div>
<div class=example style=display:none>{{ meta.example | safe }}</div>
{%- endfor -%}

<script>
let links = document.querySelectorAll('.api > .example');
for (let i = 0; i < links.length; ++i) {
	links[i].addEventListener('click', function(e) {
		const example = this.closest('.api').nextElementSibling;
		example.style.display = example.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
		e.preventDefault();
		e.stopPropagation();
	});
};
</script>
